{"word":"ἐπίρρυτος","slug":"ἐπίρρυτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπίρρυτος</b></el> <el>(ἐπίρρῠτος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐπιρρέω'><el>ἐπιρρέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>flowing in</i> or <i>to</i>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>overflowing</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>overflowed</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}